<h1>Example 1</h1>

<section>
	<p class="example-intro">All sentences must have a <b>subject</b> and a <b>verb</b>, and must express complete thoughts. Phrases without subjects provide action without actor, phrases without verbs provide actor but no action.</p>
</section>

<section>
	<h4 class="example example-sentence example-example">Adjusts the patient's medications and reviews the patient's charts. <span class="red">FRAGMENT!</span></h4>
	<p class="example example-explanation example-explanation">This phrase is a sentence fragment because it lacks a <i>subject</i>. We have an action, "Adjusts the patient's medications and reviews the patient's charts," but no actor. The thought is incomplete until we know who or what is performing the action</p>
	<h4 class="example example-corrected example-corrected">The doctor adjusts the patient's medications and reviews the patient's charts. <span class="green">SENTENCE!</span></h4>
	<p class="example corrected-explanation example-corrected-explanation">That's better! We've given our sentence a subject, the doctor, to perform our action, and we now have a complete sentence.</p>
	<button class="btn btn-large btn-primary example-button">Show Example</button>
</section>

<section>
	<h4 class="example example-sentence example-example">The nurses who worked in the intensive care unit. <span class="red">FRAGMENT!</span></h4>
	<p class="example example-explanation example-explanation">In this example we have a sentence fragment due to a lacking action. We are provided a subject, but no verb. Examples like this should remind you that sentence fragments aren't always short in length. To correct it we need to use a verb to describe an action relating to our subject.</p>
	<h4 class="example example-corrected example-corrected">The nurses who worked in the intensive care unit responded quickly and efficiently. <span class="green">SENTENCE!</span></h4>
	<p class="example corrected-explanation example-corrected-explanation">That's better! We've given our subject, the nurses, an action, responding. Now the example is a complete sentence.</p>
	<button class="btn btn-large btn-primary example-button">Show Example</button>
</section>

